# 🚀 Website Builder AI - Cursor Rules

## 🎯 Project Overview
You are working on an AI-powered website builder targeting small local businesses in Germany. The goal is to create the simplest possible website creation experience with AI-first features.

### Core Vision
- **60-second promise**: Complete website creation in under 60 seconds
- **Niche-first approach**: Start with restaurants/cafés, expand to other local businesses
- **AI-powered simplicity**: Voice-to-website, photo-to-website, chat-based editing
- **German market focus**: Local support, fair pricing (€9-39/month), German language

## 🛠️ Technology Stack

### Frontend
- **React/Next.js** for modern, fast websites
- **Tailwind CSS** for rapid styling and responsive design
- **TypeScript** for type safety and better development experience
- **React DnD** or similar for drag-and-drop functionality
- **Framer Motion** for smooth animations and transitions

### Backend
- **Node.js with Express** or **Python/Django** for API development
- **PostgreSQL** for robust data storage
- **Prisma** or **TypeORM** for database management
- **JWT** for authentication

### AI Integration
- **OpenAI GPT-4** for chat-based editing and content generation
- **Whisper API** for speech-to-text functionality
- **DALL-E/Midjourney API** for image generation
- **Google Speech API** as backup for voice features

### Hosting & Deployment
- **Vercel** or **Netlify** for automatic deployment
- **AWS S3** or **Cloudflare** for asset hosting
- **Stripe** for payment processing

## 📋 Development Guidelines

### Code Standards
- **Always use TypeScript** - no JavaScript files unless absolutely necessary
- **Follow React best practices** - functional components, hooks, proper state management
- **Use Tailwind CSS** for all styling - avoid custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
- **Implement proper error handling** - user-friendly error messages in German
- **Write responsive code** - mobile-first approach is mandatory
- **Use semantic HTML** - proper accessibility and SEO

### AI Feature Development
- **Voice features must be intuitive** - clear audio feedback, simple commands
- **Photo processing should be instant** - show progress indicators
- **Chat interface must be conversational** - natural German language responses
- **Auto-branding should be smart** - analyze business type and apply appropriate styling
- **Always provide fallback options** - if AI fails, manual editing should be available

### User Experience Principles
- **Simplicity over features** - every feature must pass the "does my grandmother understand this?" test
- **Speed is critical** - loading times under 2 seconds, instant feedback
- **German language first** - all UI text, error messages, and AI responses in German
- **Mobile-optimized** - most users will create websites on their phones
- **Progressive enhancement** - works without JavaScript, enhanced with it

## 🎨 Design System

### Color Palette
- **Primary**: Professional blue (#2563eb)
- **Secondary**: Success green (#10b981) 
- **Accent**: Warning orange (#f59e0b)
- **Neutral**: Clean grays (#6b7280, #9ca3af, #d1d5db)

### Typography
- **Headings**: Inter or Poppins (bold, clean)
- **Body**: System fonts (Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont)
- **Monospace**: JetBrains Mono for code

### Component Guidelines
- **Buttons**: Rounded corners (8px), clear hierarchy (primary/secondary/ghost)
- **Cards**: Subtle shadows, rounded corners (12px)
- **Forms**: Clear labels, helpful placeholder text, immediate validation
- **Navigation**: Simple, always visible on mobile

## 🏗️ Architecture Patterns

### Component Structure
```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── ui/           # Reusable UI components
│   ├── builder/      # Website builder specific components
│   ├── ai/          # AI-powered components
│   └── templates/   # Website templates
├── pages/
│   ├── builder/     # Builder interface
│   ├── templates/   # Template gallery
│   └── dashboard/   # User dashboard
├── hooks/           # Custom React hooks
├── utils/           # Helper functions
├── types/           # TypeScript type definitions
└── services/        # API calls and external services
```

### State Management
- **React Context** for global state (user, current website)
- **useReducer** for complex state logic
- **React Query** for server state management
- **Zustand** for simple global state if needed

### API Design
- **RESTful endpoints** with clear naming conventions
- **GraphQL** for complex queries if needed
- **Rate limiting** for AI endpoints
- **Proper error codes** and German error messages

## 🎯 Feature Development Priorities

### Phase 1 (MVP) - Months 1-2
1. **Basic drag-and-drop builder**
2. **Restaurant templates** (5 high-quality templates)
3. **Image upload and management**
4. **Text editing with AI suggestions**
5. **Domain connection**
6. **Basic payment system**

### Phase 2 (AI Features) - Month 3
1. **Chat-based editing** ("Mach den Button größer")
2. **Auto-branding** (logo generation, color schemes)
3. **Social media import** (Instagram/Facebook integration)
4. **Voice-to-text** for content creation

### Phase 3 (Premium Features) - Month 5
1. **Booking system** for restaurants
2. **Online shop module** (up to 50 products)
3. **Analytics dashboard**
4. **Multi-language support**

## 🚨 Critical Success Factors

### Performance Requirements
- **Page load time**: < 2 seconds
- **Builder responsiveness**: < 100ms for all interactions
- **AI response time**: < 3 seconds for all AI features
- **Mobile performance**: 90+ Lighthouse score

### Accessibility Standards
- **WCAG 2.1 AA compliance** - built-in accessibility
- **Keyboard navigation** - full keyboard support
- **Screen reader support** - proper ARIA labels
- **High contrast mode** - support for visual impairments

### Security Requirements
- **HTTPS everywhere** - no exceptions
- **Input sanitization** - prevent XSS attacks
- **Rate limiting** - protect against abuse
- **Data encryption** - sensitive data encrypted at rest
- **GDPR compliance** - proper data handling for German market

## 🧪 Testing Strategy

### Testing Requirements
- **Unit tests** for all utility functions and hooks
- **Integration tests** for API endpoints
- **E2E tests** for critical user flows
- **Visual regression tests** for UI components
- **Performance tests** for AI endpoints

### Test Coverage Goals
- **Minimum 80% code coverage** for business logic
- **100% coverage** for payment and authentication flows
- **Regular testing** of AI features with edge cases

## 📝 Code Review Guidelines

### Before Submitting
- **All TypeScript errors resolved**
- **No console.log statements** in production code
- **Proper error handling** implemented
- **Responsive design** tested on mobile
- **German translations** added for new UI text
- **Performance impact** considered for new features

### Review Checklist
- **Code follows established patterns**
- **No hardcoded strings** (use i18n)
- **Proper TypeScript types** defined
- **Accessibility considerations** addressed
- **Mobile-first approach** maintained
- **AI features have fallbacks**

## 🎨 Template Development

### Restaurant Template Requirements
- **Menu display** with categories and prices
- **Reservation system** integration ready
- **Photo gallery** for food images
- **Contact information** prominently displayed
- **Opening hours** clearly visible
- **QR code** for contactless menu access

### Design Principles for Templates
- **Clean and professional** appearance
- **Fast loading** with optimized images
- **Mobile-first** responsive design
- **German business culture** appropriate styling
- **Easy customization** with AI assistance

## 💡 AI Development Guidelines

### Voice Features
- **Clear audio feedback** for all voice commands
- **German language optimization** for speech recognition
- **Fallback to typing** if voice fails
- **Progress indicators** for voice processing

### Chat Interface
- **Natural German conversation** style
- **Context awareness** - remember previous commands
- **Undo/redo functionality** for AI changes
- **Confirmation prompts** for destructive actions

### Auto-Branding
- **Business type detection** from content and images
- **Color psychology** appropriate for business type
- **Professional logo generation** or placeholder suggestions
- **Consistent brand application** across all elements

## 🚀 Deployment & DevOps

### Environment Setup
- **Development**: Local development with hot reload
- **Staging**: Production-like environment for testing
- **Production**: Optimized builds with monitoring

### CI/CD Pipeline
- **Automatic testing** on pull requests
- **Code quality checks** (ESLint, Prettier, TypeScript)
- **Performance budgets** enforced
- **Automatic deployment** to staging
- **Manual approval** for production releases

### Monitoring & Analytics
- **Error tracking** with Sentry or similar
- **Performance monitoring** with Core Web Vitals
- **User analytics** (privacy-compliant)
- **AI feature usage** tracking
- **Business metrics** (conversion rates, churn)

## 🎯 Success Metrics

### Technical KPIs
- **Page load time**: < 2 seconds
- **Builder performance**: < 100ms response time
- **Uptime**: > 99.9%
- **Error rate**: < 0.1%

### Business KPIs
- **Time to website creation**: < 60 seconds
- **User satisfaction**: > 4.5/5 stars
- **Conversion rate**: > 15% free to paid
- **Churn rate**: < 5% monthly

## 🚨 Common Pitfalls to Avoid

### Technical Pitfalls
- **Over-engineering** - keep it simple
- **Ignoring mobile performance** - test on real devices
- **Poor error handling** - always provide user-friendly messages
- **Inconsistent state management** - use established patterns
- **Slow AI responses** - implement proper loading states

### Business Pitfalls
- **Feature creep** - focus on core value proposition
- **Complex pricing** - keep tiers simple and clear
- **Poor onboarding** - guide users through first website creation
- **Ignoring feedback** - regularly talk to customers
- **Scaling too fast** - ensure quality before growth

## 💬 Communication Guidelines

### Code Comments
- **Write comments in English** for technical documentation
- **User-facing text in German** with proper i18n
- **Explain complex AI logic** thoroughly
- **Document API endpoints** with examples
- **Include TODO comments** for future improvements

### Git Commit Messages
- **Use conventional commits**: feat:, fix:, docs:, style:, refactor:
- **Write in English** for technical commits
- **Include ticket numbers** if using issue tracking
- **Keep messages concise** but descriptive

## 🎯 Remember: Simplicity Wins

Every decision should be evaluated against these questions:
1. **Does this make the user experience simpler?**
2. **Would my grandmother understand this?**
3. **Does this help create a website in under 60 seconds?**
4. **Is this necessary for the MVP or can it wait?**
5. **Does this align with our German market focus?**

**Build for speed, simplicity, and the German small business owner who just wants to get online quickly and professionally.**
